On February 4, 2010, David O. Narigon submitted his resignation as Executive Vice President, Claims and Premium Audit of AMERISAFE, Inc. (the "Company"), stating that he wishes to pursue other business interests. His resignation is effective March 15, 2010. The Company does not currently plan to fill this position. The business operations reporting to Mr. Narigon will report to Geoffrey R. Banta, the Company's Chief Operating Officer.
The Company intends to negotiate a separation agreement with Mr. Narigon that will provide for severance substantially on the terms of Mr. Narigon's employment agreement with the Company. The terms of Mr. Narigon's employment agreement are described in the Company's definitive proxy statement for its 2009 annual meeting of shareholders, filed with the SEC on April 29, 2009.
